The paper focuses on the problem of data search and discovery, which is a common issue in information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The study also involves interviews with data seekers, which suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) perspective. Additionally, the paper discusses the design of data discovery systems, which is related to database systems (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
